        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/12614\">#12614</a> is another issue that's entirely about design -- choosing an appropriate color with the right contrast properties, or some other design that simultaneously highlights the text and keeps it readable. It's in the zulip/zulip repo, but I found it just now because it was originally reported on mobile, as <a href=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip-mobile/pull/3531\">#M3531</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I have tried different combinations and came up with two. I think the red one is better as it shows good contrast with all three colors (dark-background, white text, blue links) and also defines the word 'alert'... What do you think <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"2187\">@Greg Price</span> ?</p>\n<p>Present:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/52/GMkd3sjyxuHnYjR88q21CvYr/Present.png\">Present.png</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/52/GMkd3sjyxuHnYjR88q21CvYr/Present.png\" title=\"Present.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/52/GMkd3sjyxuHnYjR88q21CvYr/Present.png\"></a></div><p>Red (#691d1c):<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/55/gVa5WEJhN_cQYC0b6HBXGVeS/691d1c.png\">691d1c.png</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/55/gVa5WEJhN_cQYC0b6HBXGVeS/691d1c.png\" title=\"691d1c.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/55/gVa5WEJhN_cQYC0b6HBXGVeS/691d1c.png\"></a></div><p>Purple (#d700ff4d):<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/f3/nEx-IREmZZP4tkJmO4xrPGTm/d700ff4d.png\">d700ff4d.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/f3/nEx-IREmZZP4tkJmO4xrPGTm/d700ff4d.png\" title=\"d700ff4d.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/f3/nEx-IREmZZP4tkJmO4xrPGTm/d700ff4d.png\"></a></div>",
